.TH NHOPKG-SRC 8 "@RELEASEDATE@" "@PACKAGE_VERSION@" "Nhopkg Manual"
.SH NAME
nhopkg-src \- create, validate, and build source package projects for nhopkg
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nhopkg-src
\fB\-\-init\fR [\fIname\fR]
.br
.B nhopkg-src
\fB\-\-createpackage\fR [\fB\-\-force\fR]
.br
.B nhopkg-src
\fB\-\-buildpackage\fR
.br
.B nhopkg-src
\fB\-\-validate\fR [\fIfile\fR]
.br
.B nhopkg-src
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
.br
.B nhopkg-src
\fB\-\-version\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBnhopkg-src\fR creates, validates, and builds source package projects for nhopkg.
It works with \fI.srcnho\fR files \(em flat tarballs containing the \fInhoid\fR metadata
file plus patches and extra files, which \fBnhopkg \-bv\fR uses to download, compile,
and install binary packages.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B \-\-init [\fIname\fR]
Create a new source package project interactively.
.br
If \fIname\fR is provided on the command line, it is used as the package name
(and project directory). Otherwise the tool prompts for it.
.br
Prompts are asked interactively with sensible defaults:
.RS
.IP \(bu 4
Version (1.0)
.IP \(bu 4
Release (1)
.IP \(bu 4
Category (apps)
.IP \(bu 4
Group (base)
.IP \(bu 4
Repository (extra)
.IP \(bu 4
Description
.IP \(bu 4
Maintainer
.IP \(bu 4
Packager
.IP \(bu 4
URL (project home page)
.IP \(bu 4
Download URL (Packageurl)
.IP \(bu 4
Git reference (Packageref, required for git sources)
.IP \(bu 4
SHA256 checksum (optional; can be downloaded automatically)
.IP \(bu 4
License
.IP \(bu 4
Architecture (set to machine architecture)
.IP \(bu 4
Provides / Conflicts (optional)
.RE
.P
The project directory contains:
.RS
.IP \(bu 4
\fInhoid\fR \(em the source recipe metadata file
.IP \(bu 4
\fIpatches/\fR \(em directory for patch files (*.patch, *.diff)
.IP \(bu 4
\fIothers/\fR \(em directory for extra files
.IP \(bu 4
\fIsources/\fR \(em downloaded tarballs (excluded from .srcnho)
.IP \(bu 4
\fIbuild/\fR \(em build artifacts (excluded from .srcnho)
.RE
.P
If the download URL has a known extension (.tar.gz, .tar.xz, .tar.bz2,
.tar.zst, .tgz, .tar, .zip), the tarball is downloaded to \fIsources/\fR.

.TP
.B \-\-createpackage [\fB\-\-force\fR]
Package the current project directory into a \fI.srcnho\fR file.
.br
The output file is named \fI<name>-<version>-<release>.srcnho\fR.
.br
\fB\-\-force\fR overwrites an existing output file without prompting.

.TP
.B \-\-buildpackage
Build the \fI.srcnho\fR package by running \fBnhopkg \-bv\fR with \fBsudo \-k\fR.
.br
The tool determines the expected .srcnho filename by reading the nhoid metadata
in the current directory. Always prompts for sudo credentials.

.TP
.B \-\-validate [\fIfile\fR]
Validate a .srcnho package or the nhoid file in the current directory.
.br
If no file is given, validates \fInhoid\fR in the current directory.
.br
Checks performed:
.RS
.IP \(bu 4
Extension is .srcnho (or current dir has nhoid)
.IP \(bu 4
Tarball extractable
.IP \(bu 4
nhoid file exists and has correct header (%NHO-0.5)
.IP \(bu 4
Name, Version, Release fields are present and non-empty
.IP \(bu 4
nbuild() function exists and is not noemptyfuncs
.IP \(bu 4
ninstall() (or ninstall_<part>() variants) exist and are not noemptyfuncs
.IP \(bu 4
npostinstall() and npostremove() may be noemptyfuncs
.IP \(bu 4
All split parts defined in Parts: have corresponding ninstall_<part>()
.IP \(bu 4
No duplicate function definitions
.IP \(bu 4
Warns if sha256 is missing
.IP \(bu 4
Warns if Packageref is missing for git sources
.IP \(bu 4
Warns if Description is empty
.RE
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-force
With \fB\-\-createpackage\fR, overwrite existing .srcnho file without prompting.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Create a new project
.B nhopkg-src \-\-init myapp
.TP
Package the project
.B nhopkg-src \-\-createpackage
.TP
Build the package
.B nhopkg-src \-\-buildpackage
.TP
Validate the result
.B nhopkg-src \-\-validate myapp-1.0-1.srcnho
.SH FILES
.TP
.I nhoid
Source recipe metadata file in the project directory.
.TP
.I patches/*.patch, patches/*.diff
Patch files applied during build.
.TP
.I others/*
Extra files included in the .srcnho (e.g. desktop files, icons).
.TP
.I sources/
Downloaded tarballs (excluded from .srcnho).
.TP
.I build/
Build artifacts (excluded from .srcnho).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR nhopkg (8),
.BR nhopkg.conf (5)
.SH AUTHOR
Jaime Gil de Sagredo Luna <jaimegildesagredo@gmail.com>
